column5: Havent been on here alot recently, found my self just spending what ever free time i have going out fishing anything. been fun, learned alot and seen places i havent been before yet, most of these fish were from a river of some sort( i like river fishing ) anyways heres a few for recap.                gotta love river bass!                        anyone know why this perch has dots all over?      some for my grandparents =)
nice report, lots of good looking fish.  are those browns mature fish, or yearlings.  really cool looking fish tambo
adult resident trout. they stay and live in the creeks rather than going out to get big out in the lake.

The black spots are just that a parasite called black spot. Carried in bird poo thrives in warm water. Harmless its just in the skin. Its a good indicator that the fish is living in a stressful enviroment.
Way to go on thoes river smallies! My biggest from a little river was close to 4 pounds.
This smallie looks tired or pissed at your spinner
Beauty report l2p That's a good mix bag of fish you got yoursefl into!!! Thanks for sharing Leechman
